rt IV D’AILLY于大约1335年出生时，他的父亲Robert III d'Ailly le Haut Clocher31岁，母亲Marie Marguerite de Picquigny20岁。他于1374年与Marie d'Auxy在法国豪-德-福朗斯帕-德-卡拉斯奧勒-a奧结婚。他们至少是2个女儿的父母。他去世于1369年享年35岁。"},"hr":{"about 1335–1369":"oko 1335.–1369.","1332–Female":"1332–preminula","1335–1369":"1335–1369.","1342–Female":"1342–preminula","1343–1415":"1343–1415","1344–1408":"1344–1408","1350–1415":"1350–1415","–1405":"–1405","–1413":"–1413","1305–1384":"1305–1384","1316–1367":"1316–1367.","1384":"1384","1350":"1350","1316":"1316","1305":"1305","1415":"1415","1369":"1369.","1413":"1413","20 November 1342":"20. studenog 1342.","1335":"1335","1367":"1367.","1344":"1344","1343":"1343","1332":"1332","1342":"1342","about 1335":"oko 1335.","1408":"1408","1405":"1405","Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, France":"Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, Francuska"},"cs":{"about 1335–1369":"okolo 1335–1369","1332–Female":"1332–Zesnulá","1335–1369":"1335–1369","1342–Female":"1342–Zesnulá","1343–1415":"1343–1415","1344–1408":"1344–1408","1350–1415":"1350–1415","–1405":"–1405","–1413":"–1413","1305–1384":"1305–1384","1316–1367":"1316–1367","1384":"1384","1350":"1350","1316":"1316","1305":"1305","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1413":"1413","20 November 1342":"20. listopadu 1342","1335":"1335","1367":"1367","1344":"1344","1343":"1343","1332":"1332","1342":"1342","about 1335":"okolo 1335","1408":"1408","1405":"1405","Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, France":"Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, Francie"},"da":{"about 1335–1369":"omkring 1335–1369","1332–Female":"1332–Afdød","1335–1369":"1335–1369","1342–Female":"1342–Afdød","1343–1415":"1343–1415","1344–1408":"1344–1408","1350–1415":"1350–1415","–1405":"–1405","–1413":"–1413","1305–1384":"1305–1384","1316–1367":"1316–1367","1384":"1384","1350":"1350","1316":"1316","1305":"1305","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1413":"1413","20 November 1342":"20. november 1342","1335":"1335","1367":"1367","1344":"1344","1343":"1343","1332":"1332","1342":"1342","about 1335":"omkring 1335","1408":"1408","1405":"1405","Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, France":"Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, Frankrig"},"nl":{"about 1335–1369":"circa 1335–1369","1332–Female":"1332–Overleden","1335–1369":"1335–1369","1342–Female":"1342–Overleden","1343–1415":"1343–1415","1344–1408":"1344–1408","1350–1415":"1350–1415","–1405":"–1405","–1413":"–1413","1305–1384":"1305–1384","1316–1367":"1316–1367","1384":"1384","1350":"1350","1316":"1316","1305":"1305","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1413":"1413","20 November 1342":"20 november 1342","1335":"1335","1367":"1367","1344":"1344","1343":"1343","1332":"1332","1342":"1342","about 1335":"circa 1335","1408":"1408","1405":"1405","Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, France":"Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"about 1335–1369":"about 1335–1369","1332–Female":"1332–Deceased","1335–1369":"1335–1369","1342–Female":"1342–Deceased","1343–1415":"1343–1415","1344–1408":"1344–1408","1350–1415":"1350–1415","–1405":"–1405","–1413":"–1413","1305–1384":"1305–1384","1316–1367":"1316–1367","1384":"1384","1350":"1350","1316":"1316","1305":"1305","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1413":"1413","20 November 1342":"20 November 1342","1335":"1335","1367":"1367","1344":"1344","1343":"1343","1332":"1332","1342":"1342","about 1335":"about 1335","1408":"1408","1405":"1405","Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, France":"Ailly-le-Haut-Clocher, Somme, Picardie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"D’AILLY","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["(2010: NA)","Scottish and Irish: mainly Scottish variant of Irish   Daly  .","Scottish (of Norman origin): variant of   Dally   2, a cognate of 3 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Daly","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Kieran, Dermot, Brigid, Aileen, Declan, Finbarr, Fintan, Aidan, Brennan, Bridie, Cathal.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Dálaigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Dálach</i>’, a personal name based on <i>dál</i> (modern <i>dáil</i>) ‘meeting, assembly’.","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Dally   2."]},{"name":"Alyea","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>D'Ailly</b> or   Dailly  . Compare   Allee   2 and   Elyea  .","History: This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with several variants, including <i>Allée</i>, and the original form <i>d'Ailly</i>). The Huguenot ancestor was Nicolas d'Ailly, who came from France to NY <i>c.</i> 1682 via the Netherlands and England and died in NJ <i>c.</i> 1700."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"IV","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Violet  ,   Vivien  , or   Vivian ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vivien","meanings":["Earlier generally taken as a variant of the boy's name   Vivian  , but now also rarely used for boys. This spelling was quite common in Old French. Its use as a girl's name in the English-speaking world was influenced by  Tennyson's  Merlin and Vivien (  1859 ). This name, from Arthurian legend, may represent an altered form of a Celtic name (perhaps akin to the Irish Gaelic name <i>Béibhinn</i> ‘white lady’, pronounced ‘bee-<b>veen</b>’). The actress  Vivien Leigh  (  1913–67 ) was christened <i>Vivian</i>."]},{"name":"Violet","meanings":["From the name of the flower (Old French <i>violette</i>, Late Latin <i>violetta</i>, a diminutive of <i>viola</i>). This was one of the earliest flower names to become popular in Britain, being used as early as  1700  and becoming well established in the 19th century, although it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert IV D’AILLY was born about 1335, his father, Robert III d'Ailly le Haut Clocher, was 31 and his mother, Marie Marguerite de Picquigny, was 20. He married Marie d'Auxy in 1374, in Auxi-le-Château, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1369, at the age of 35."},"et":{"about 1335–1369":"umbes 1335–1369","1332–Female":"1332–Surnud","1335–1369":"1335–1369","1342–Female":"1342–Surnud","1343–1415":"1343–1415","1344–1408":"1344–1408","1350–1415":"1350–1415","–1405":"–1405","–1413":"–1413","1305–1384":"1305–1384","1316–1367":"1316–1367","1384":"1384","1350":"1350","1316":"1316","1305":"1305","1415":"1415","1369":"1369","1413":"1413","20 November 1342":"20. november 1342","1335":"1335","1367":"1367","1344":"1344","1343":"1343","1332":"1332","1342":"1342","about 1335":"umbes 1335","1408":"1408","1405":"1405","Ailly-le-Haut-Cloche